description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to gain experience as an Occupational Therapist within the Occupational Therapy service in the East area of the Betsi Cadwaladr University Health Board. Rotations include medical, stroke, community hospital, acute and older persons mental health service and community mental health teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Heather McNaught Clinical Lead Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01978 725412&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;heather.mcnaught@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
